          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A gold  cylinder  of  diameter  1.232cm  and   height",
                " 1.257cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLATE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 200 mum thick Ilford C-2 emulsion. The  plane",
                " of  each  emulsion was vertical and made an angle of",
                " 5.degr.  to the line  joining  the  centres  of  the",
                " target and the emulsion.  Lead shields 0.32 cm thick",
                " were placed over each emulsion to screen it from low",
                " energy photons from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The data were corrected for:",
                " (a) the shrinkage of the emulsion,",
                " (b)  the tracks which leave the emulsion,",
                " (c) the  attenuation  of neutrons in the gold target",
                " and the lead shield round the emulsion,",
                " (d) the   variation  of  the  n-p  scattering  cross",
                "     section with neutron energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors are presented."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The error involved in  normalising  the  fast",
                " and slow scan, which is 7.5% ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The experimental spectrum is compared with the",
                " energy distribution calculated on the basis  of  the",
                " evaporation model.",
                "A  new method for the calculation of the  corrections",
                " involved  for  those  proton recoils which leave the",
                " emulsion is presented."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The spectrum shows two peaks.  The large peak at 1.25",
                " MeV can be interpreted as  due  to  the  statistical",
                " decay  of  the compound nucleus. The smaller peak at",
                " about 5.5 MeV is  assumed  to  came  from  a  direct",
                " transition, as described by the Wilkinson model."
              ]
            }
          ],
